reviews.review_text: Short but sweet I must say this is one of the best crazy fingers I've ever heard.  The quiet space intro into the other into china doll is amazing also.  One of my favorite shows!

Lysergic show A very trippy show from the wildly inconsistent year of 1986 and let's face it 86 deserves its less than stellar reputation. However this little gem is a real winner. It's not a very long show but it's a strong one. Jerry and company are on and in a psychedelic mood. Very nice Crazy Fingers> Playing>Drums/Space jam sandwich featuring an intense Other One that starts acapella out of space and leads to an eerie China Doll that reminds me in mood of the '69 versions of Mountains Of The Moon. Very nice. Sugar Magnolia and The Mighty Quinn lift the mood a bit and sends the listener out on a positive vibe.
86 Gem Highlights:  Playing In The Band, Drums, Space, The Other One, China Doll, Playing In The Band

1986 goodnes The year 1986 was not great, especially vs 85-84-83 etc. This show is the exception a 22m long playing that's rocking the whole time by the whole band! I'm surprised it's not more loved! 

Also a opening Crazy Fingers!
